The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Sex video
                                                                                                            Sex video
                            
	Kuala Lumpur, Jan. 5 (PTI): Two ethnic Indians were among four persons arrested for allegedly selling and distributing a sex video purportedly featuring a former Malaysian minister.        
	Chua Soi Lek had resigned from the health ministry soon after the widely circulated DVDs shocked the nation.        
	The Indians, believed to be hawkers of pirated videos, were selling the discs for 10 ringgit (Rs 110), claiming they contained clips of Chuas escapade with an unidentified woman.        
	But the buyers found that the DVDs did not contain the actual footage but a 13-minute clip showed Chua admitting to the act that had been reported by a TV news channel, a member of the Malaysian Chinese Association was quoted by a local Chinese daily as saying.                                                                                                                                                                            
